instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin runs the ACC Controlling FE, which identifies the lead vehicle and computes a desired speed. The computed speed is transmitted back to the vehicle where the Actuation FE converts the speed command into motor voltage signals to drive the vehicle. Remote‑management commands issued from the User Interface FE (control panel) – enable/disable ACC, set desired speed, emergency brake – are also sent to the Actuation FE. Commands travel over the same Wi‑Fi/UDP link and are packaged by the Data Translation FE. Validation, authentication and conflict‑resolution mechanisms are not described in the provided documents, nor is an explicit acknowledgement of command execution; the system relies on actuation feedback displayed in the UI."
]

